        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Jan. 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Phillips</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I have received this morning your very kind present;<ref target="#foot.f2"/> but I am almost ashamed to accept so beautiful a book in return for my old &amp; dry works on Rocks.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>With very sincere thanks. Believe me. Yours very truly | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 a] <hi rend="italic">added</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Dated by the relationship to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1822.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Phillips, 18 January [1856]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Phillips 1855. CD’s copy is in the Darwin Library–Down. The work includes a series of views of Yorkshire taken from sketches by Phillips.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><hi rend="italic">Geology of ‘Beagle’</hi>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1822.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Phillips, 18 January [1856]</ref>, n. 6.</note>
        </div>        
            
